To access the full name of the country and port when the user enters the first country name and selects from the suggestion list, you can use the following JavaScript code:

```
const searchField = document.querySelector('.ant-input.ant-select-search_field');

searchField.addEventListener('input', (e) => {
  const inputValue = e.target.value;
  const options = document.querySelectorAll('.ant-select-dropdown-menu-item');
  options.forEach((option) => {
    if (option.textContent.toLowerCase().includes(inputValue.toLowerCase())) {
      option.style.display = 'block';
    } else {
      option.style.display = 'none';
    }
  });
});

document.querySelectorAll('.ant-select-dropdown-menu-item').forEach((option) => {
  option.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
    const selectedValue = e.target.textContent;
    console.log('Selected Value:', selectedValue);
    // Add your logic here to handle the selected value
  });
});
```

In this code:

1. We first add an event listener to the search field to filter the options based on the input value.
2. Then, we add an event listener to each option to listen for click events.
3. When an option is clicked, we get the selected value (full country and port name) and log it to the console.
4. You can add your logic to handle the selected value.

